node.text:
⁣Hi gorgeous people, ⠀
⠀
Is knitwear also your favourite things to wear on those cooler days when you just want to be warm and cosy? 🙏🧶⠀
⠀
Knits are definitely one of those fashion items which make you comfortable and effortlessly stylish. They are diverse and you can match them with your favourite flows dress or pair of pants just like me on this picture.⠀
⠀
I would suggest to stay away from damagingly polyester or acrylic if you can… search for recycled wool or organic cotton…⠀
⠀
If you practising eco-friendly styling, it is important to pick up and select few stand up items. Keep your clothes low effort basic and mix match them with stand out items ⠀
when you need something new, source it, send to a charity or vintage store and practice different styling tactics…⠀
Try to have fever clothes, collections supporting our planet. Keep on shopping consciously… these are my go green simple steps I’m practising as much as possible. ⠀
⠀
Do you look out for fabrics that treat the planet right when purchasing knitwear? Can’t wait to read your comments below. 🤗🤩 ⠀
⠀
Outfit details: ⠀
Sweater: handmade knitwear ⠀
Leather pants: preloved @dior ⠀
Sandals: preloved @ralphlauren ⠀
⠀
⠀
⠀

node.text:
⁣Capsule wardrobe 1970 susie Faux, London boutique owner popularized in 1980’s by designer Donna Karan⠀
⠀
“all clothes in the wardrobe serve a specific purpose and go well together to achieve a maximum number of different, yet personal style-consistent outfits. meaning that you always look put together and outfits will reflect your personal signature style”⠀
⠀
every wardrobe should be a capsule wardrobe…🙏
* it is not what the other people are telling you to have in your wardrobe, it it all about you! 💫🤩
* it is a very personal thing!⠀
every women is unique, have and live different lives, our clothes should fit those lives⠀
* your wardrobe should have sufficient pieces for you to go according to your lifestyle, you should have clothes which are necessary, meaning every item in your wardrobe should have purpose and suit your lifestyle⠀
* if it doesn't fit the purpose, then you are wasting the precious space in your wardrobe⠀
* the amount of the items you need depends purely on your life style! so your wardrobe should be build around your lifestyle, where you live, what type of clothing you like, what is your personal style, and the endless combinations…⠀
⠀
I love fashion, in fashion you can be creative, express your self, but this should not come at the price of overflowing wardrobes with unworn clothes. 🙏👏🌍⠀
⠀
Together we make a difference! 💥⠀
⠀
⠀

⁣I graduated as a primary school teacher, ended up working as cabin crew for a world leading airline. Took me some time to find out what I truly wanted. Never give up and follow your dreams… ☺️🥰🤩⠀
⠀
From a young age I used to mix and match clothes, started fulfilling my passion by helping my friends and family members in choosing their outfits. 🥳⠀
⠀
I have always been obsessed with clothes, fashion. My account is about sharing different styles, so you can better understand your style personality, which changes with time as you recognize that you have been a different personality at another stage in your life…🤗
⠀
My passion is to help you feeling amazing on the outside and inside. To become Stylish and Confident and have a Worry-Free Wardrobe…⠀
I believe everyone can look fabulous! 😊👏🙏⠀
⠀
I truly focus on supporting small ethical, sustainable brands. I adore second-hand and preloved fashion as it is better for the planet and it is so much more fun…🌿🌍♻️

Blessings, Eva 💙♥️🧡💚💛

node.text:
⁣Sharing with you some TIPS HOW TO SAVE MONEY AND LOOK THE BEST🥰
* DON’T BUY CLOTHES FOR ONE OCCASION⠀
have few dressier pieces in your wardrobe, something classy rather than trend-led. ⠀
you can use accessories to create an occasional look, or rent a dress. ⠀⠀
* DON’T BUY, KEEP CLOTHES WHICH DOESN’T FIT YOU⠀
always be realistic and honest with yourself, if it doesn't fit donate or sell it. ⠀
don’t keep or buy small size clothes as a motivation for weight loss or on sale⠀⠀
* DON’T BUY, KEEP CLOTHES WHICH DOESN’T SUIT YOU⠀
don’t buy clothes which you love on someone else or trendy pieces which don’t suit you⠀
clothes have to make you confident and comfortable⠀
* WHEN YOU BUY SOMETHING GET RID OF SOMETHING ELSE⠀
apply the ONE-IN and ONE-OUT rule⠀
it will keep your shelves, rails from overflowing and it will help you to be much confident what you are purchasing⠀
* DON’T BUY LOT OF THINGS AT ONCE⠀
when we feel like we hate everything in our wardrobes and we have nothing to wear⠀
keep pieces you love and note of the things you are lacking⠀
it’s a constant evolving process, buy one really nice piece every month for more stylish wardrobe⠀
* MAKE SOME TOUGH DECISIONS⠀
nobody likes throwing things away, sometimes it means letting go off memories, no need to hold on on something you haven't wear for decades⠀
if you really can’t say goodbye some clothes, put them on trial and see how many times you wear it in the next 6 months⠀
*CREATE A UNIFORM⠀
make the most of the knowledge of what suits you, what you look good in, keep it simple, buy something what you already own⠀
* KNOW YOUR WARDROBE INSIDE OUT⠀
before you go for shopping you won’t have an accident to buy something you don't need⠀
* GET YOUR DAMAGED CLOTHES FIXED OR TAILOR YOUR OWN PIECES⠀
* DON’T UNDERESTIMATE THE POWER OF A CAPSULE WARDROBE⠀
you need very little to look good⠀
look after you clothes, you can do it with just 15 pieces.⠀
⠀
⠀
